          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-03-31 22:37:43" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(extension of meaning of {L:τέκνον&lt;SDBG:τέκνον:000000&gt;}[a] ‘child, offspring,’ {D:10.36}) a person of any age for whom there is a special relationship of endearment and association</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>my child</Gloss>
                <Gloss>my dear friend</Gloss>
                <Gloss>my dear man</Gloss>
                <Gloss>my dear one</Gloss>
                <Gloss>my dear lad</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It may be impossible to translate τεκνία literally as ‘my children’ in  {S:06200300700002} since this might suggest a kinship relationship between the author of 1 John and the people to whom he is addressing his letter. A more satisfactory equivalent in some languages is often ‘my dear friends’ or ‘my dear ones.’</Comments>
